  <discussion>Clethra tomentosa flowers later than C. alnifolia when the two are grown together;
        it has long been treated as a species in Europe (J. D. Wann 1997), where it has been
        cultivated since about 1850. Although leaf blade dimensions are essentially the same in the
        two species, C. tomentosa has consistently shorter petioles, woolly-tomentose new shoots,
        and shorter, hairy styles.</discussion>
